                            <comment id="13726739" author="jkrupan" created="Thu, 1 Aug 2013 18:54:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds like this might resolve &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4304&quot; title=&quot;Coupling between SpellCheckComponent(s) and QueryConverter(s) is a mess and makes no sense&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4304&quot;&gt;SOLR-4304&lt;/a&gt; - &quot;NPE in Solr SpellCheckComponent if more than one QueryConverter&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13744142" author="hossman" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2013 19:51:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jack: I think it will sort of &quot;fix&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4304&quot; title=&quot;Coupling between SpellCheckComponent(s) and QueryConverter(s) is a mess and makes no sense&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4304&quot;&gt;SOLR-4304&lt;/a&gt; in that i &lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt; I can make it so that instead of getting an NPE at request time, you&apos;ll get an error on startup that you can&apos;t have multiple queryConvertors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but in general the way queryConvertors are configured/initialized seems to be a giant pile of crap &amp;#8211; i&apos;ll post more details in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4304&quot; title=&quot;Coupling between SpellCheckComponent(s) and QueryConverter(s) is a mess and makes no sense&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4304&quot;&gt;SOLR-4304&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13744292" author="hossman" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2013 21:42:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;requires usage of loadPluginInfo to specify if multiple PluginInfo instances are expected else error&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;makes getPluginInfo fail if multiple PluginInfo instances exist&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds a test for a good error if multiple instances of directoryFactory are found (as an example)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fixes a bug in solrconfig-test-misc.xml that actually did have redundent directoryFactories configured.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
